snippet.textDisplay:
Wilder does talk a lot of shit, HOWEVER, no one is factoring how skinny his legs are.

No matter how strong he is or thinks he is, wearing a 40lbs costume when your adrenaline and nerves are sky high walking into the biggest fight of your life is a bad move and it WILL wear down your legs significantly quicker than it would in training.

On top of that Wilder’s weight was around a career high so that wasn’t doing him any favours either since he cannot carry that body weight around comfortably.

What I found hilarious was the shocked look on his face in round 1 when Fury actually came at him! Wilder is so deluded he thought there was no way Fury would do it.

Underestimating a world class fighter... well done Deontay!

What we can take from this is that Wilder is a remarkably stupid man and from what I hear he’s now blaming his coach saying his coach was undercover agent from Fury’s team.
